Business Brief -- Cincinnati Bell Inc.:
   Company Posts 36% Drop
   In Net for Its 1st Period
Cincinnati Bell noted that growth in local phone access
lines slowed to 1% in 1991, the slowest rate of growth since
the 1982 recession.
   Earnings for 1991 fell 53% to $42.7 million, or 63 cents a
share, from $91 million, or $1.44 a share, in 1990. Revenue
grew 7.4% $1.1 billion from $1 billion.
   Cincinnati Bell shares were quoted at $19.25, down 25
cents, in late New York Stock Exchange composite trading.